solution.p:
Factor f(x): 
                     f(x) &= \frac{x^2-4}{x^4-7x^3+10x^2} 
                     &= \frac{(x+2)(x-2)}{x^2(x^2-7x+10)} 
                     &= \frac{(x+2)(x-2)}{x^2(x-2)(x-5)} 
                     &= \frac{x+2}{x^2(x-5)}, \quad x \ne 2
                 There is a removable discontinuity at x=2 with limit \lim_{x \to 2} f(x) = \lim_{x \to 2} \frac{x+2}{x^2(x-5)} = \frac{4}{4(-3)} = -\frac{1}{3}. There are infinite discontinuities at x=0 and x=5 corresponding to vertical asymptotes.

